## 🧪 3. Robust Test Cases & Self-Diagnostics
* **Programmatic Assertions**: For every complex visual feature or backend service integration, implement a self-diagnostic assertions run panel (e.g. a "Diagnostics: PASSED/FAILED" test block) to allow administrators or testers to verify the system directly from the admin panel.
* **Edge Cases**: Prevent failures around missing properties, null bounds, undefined references, and offline states by adding fallback parameters (e.g. `Math.max(50, val)` or safe chain operators `?.`).
* **Zero Warnings**: Ensure all modifications compile successfully and pass build routines (`npm run build`) without warning outputs.
